● Summary: GraphContextNode Implementation

  Implemented GraphContextNode TypedDict to provide ~90% type safety for get_domain_context_raw() return values.

  The Tension Resolved:
  Cross-domain graph queries return heterogeneous data from 15+ domains. Full typing would require a union of all domain models (unwieldy). GraphContextNode captures the common graph traversal fields that ALL entities share, with an
   escape hatch for domain-specific data.

  Files Modified:

  1. core/services/protocols/base_protocols.py (lines 81-132)
    - Added GraphContextNode TypedDict with typed fields:
        - uid: str - Entity UID
      - labels: list[str] - Neo4j labels
      - distance: int - Hops from source
      - path_strength: float - Confidence cascade
      - via_relationships: list[str] - Relationship path
      - title: str - Common optional field
      - entity_type: str - EntityType value when available
      - raw_properties: dict[str, Any] - Escape hatch for domain-specific data
    - Updated get_domain_context_raw() return type from list[dict[str, Any]] to list[GraphContextNode]
  2. adapters/persistence/neo4j/universal_backend.py
    - Added import for GraphContextNode
    - Updated method signature and docstring
  3. core/services/protocols/__init__.py
    - Added GraphContextNode to imports and __all__

  Usage Pattern (unchanged for consumers):
  result = await backend.get_domain_context_raw(...)
  for node in result.value:
      uid = node["uid"]  # Now type-safe: str
      labels = node["labels"]  # Now type-safe: list[str]
      # Domain-specific via raw_properties escape hatch
